summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Oregon and Washington Railroad Company, a corporation, to the City of Georgetown (now The City of Seattle), dated February 8th, 1910, to certain portions of Blocks One (1), Two (2) and Seven (7), in Maples Addition to The City of Seattle; and portion of Block Eleven (11), Commercial Street Stream Motor Addition, an Addition to The City of Seattle; situate in the County of King, State of Washington, to be used for street purposes only.
